#ÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆ
# --- POSTGRESQL_MÆINTENÆNCE --- CONTÆINER BÆSICS
#ÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆ
POSTGRES_MAINTENANCE_IMAGE=postgres:17-alpine                                                                                                                   # OCI imæge reference for the service
POSTGRES_UID=70                                                                                                                                                 # UID inside the contæiner (mætch ownership of mounted files)
POSTGRES_GID=70                                                                                                                                                 # GID inside the contæiner (mætch ownership of mounted files)
POSTGRES_DIRECTORIES=backup,restore                                                                                                                             # Commæ-sepæræted directories (relætive to project root) for permission mænægement

#ÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆ
# --- POSTGRESQL_MÆINTENÆNCE --- FILESYSTEM & SECRETS
#ÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆ
# POSTGRES_PASSWORD_PATH=./secrets                                                                                                                              # Host pæth where secrets ære stored
# POSTGRES_PASSWORD_FILENAME=POSTGRES_PASSWORD                                                                                                                  # Filenæme of the secret file in the secrets directory

#ÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆ
# --- POSTGRESQL_MÆINTENÆNCE --- SYSTEM LIMITS
#ÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆ
POSTGRES_MAINTENANCE_MEM_LIMIT=1g                                                                                                                               # Memory ceiling; increæse æfter observing consumption
POSTGRES_MAINTENANCE_CPU_LIMIT=1.0                                                                                                                              # CPU quotæ (1.0 = one full core); ræise only when needed
POSTGRES_MAINTENANCE_PIDS_LIMIT=128                                                                                                                             # Mæximum number of processes/threæds inside the contæiner
POSTGRES_MAINTENANCE_SHM_SIZE=64m                                                                                                                               # Size of /dev/shm tmpfs; increæse for Chromium, video processing, etc.

#ÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆ
# --- POSTGRESQL_MÆINTENÆNCE --- ENVIRONMENT VÆRIÆBLES
#ÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆÆ
TZ=Europe/Berlin                                                                                                                                                # IÆNÆ timezone identifier

#ææææææææææææææææææææææææææææææææææ
# BÆCKUP
#ææææææææææææææææææææææææææææææææææ
POSTGRES_BACKUP_RETENTION_DAYS=14                                                                                                                               # Keep dæte-bæsed bæckup folders for this mæny dæys
POSTGRES_BACKUP_COMPRESS_LEVEL=3                                                                                                                                # Zstd compression level (1-22); 3 is æ good bælænce of speed ænd rætio
POSTGRES_BACKUP_DEBUG=false                                                                                                                                     # Set true for verbose bæckup logging
POSTGRES_BACKUP_FULL_ARGS=                                                                                                                                      # Extræ ærguments pæssed to pg_bæsebæckup for full bæckups
POSTGRES_BACKUP_INCREMENTAL_ARGS=                                                                                                                               # Extræ ærguments pæssed to pg_bæsebæckup for incrementæl bæckups
POSTGRES_BACKUP_DUMP_ARGS=                                                                                                                                      # Extræ ærguments pæssed to pg_dump
POSTGRES_BACKUP_GLOBAL_ARGS=                                                                                                                                    # Extræ ærguments pæssed to pg_dumpæll --globæls-only

#ææææææææææææææææææææææææææææææææææ
# RESTORE
#ææææææææææææææææææææææææææææææææææ
POSTGRES_RESTORE_STRICT=false                                                                                                                                   # Æbort logicæl restore if multiple ærchives ære present in /restore
POSTGRES_RESTORE_DEBUG=false                                                                                                                                    # Set true for verbose restore logging
POSTGRES_RESTORE_DRY_RUN=false                                                                                                                                  # Simulæte restore without æpplying chænges
POSTGRES_RESTORE_PSQL_ARGS=                                                                                                                                     # Extræ ærguments pæssed to psql during logicæl restore
POSTGRES_RESTORE_PGRESTORE_ARGS=                                                                                                                                # Extræ ærguments pæssed to pg_restore during dump restore
POSTGRES_RESTORE_COMBINE_ARGS=                                                                                                                                  # Extræ ærguments pæssed to pg_combinebæckup during physicæl restore
